      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Artwork and Exhibitions</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Artwork and Exhibitions series provides an overview of Castagnacci's art, his work in the studio, and promotional materials for several exhibitions. Catalogs from exhibits in 1989 and 1996 explore the variations and underlying ideas of his work. Video footage of his collaboration with percussionist and University of Michigan faculty member Michael Gould captures the early conversations and experiments that led to their 2006 exhibition. Digital reproductions represent various phases of his drawings and paintings, including his series "Bend in the Road," "Four Corners," "Isola di Giglio," "Rome Variations," and "Stereotomia," among others. Still images also document the display of his "Rome Monotypes" and a 2004 show at Kalamazoo College's Light Fine Arts Gallery. Three videos from 2004 depict Castagnacci at work on a printing press and giving a tour of artwork in his studio. Promotional materials include a PowerPoint for his 2010 show "Notes from a Quarry" at the River Gallery in Dexter, Michigan as well as several flyers from other exhibitions.</p>
