      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Interviews and Background Materials</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Interviews and Background Materials series contains materials that contextualize Castagnacci's work as a professor and artist. Still images document the quarries and seascapes of Gloucester, Massachusetts as well as Italian street scenes and architectural features that are reflected in his work. Videos provide insight into Castagnacci's personal influences and experiences and include interviews of him by videographer Peter Knox and artist Kevin Brady; a narrated visit to Halibut Point Quarry; and conversations with two of his mentors, the artists Bernard Chaet and Ralph Coburn. The series also includes<title render="italic">Personal Bedrock</title> , a biographical video by Peter Knox that explores the evolution of Castagnacci's artistic philosophy and his creative work.</p>
        </scopecontent>
